absorption:
The absolute bioavailability of ponatinib is unknown. Peak concentrations of ponatinib are observed within 6 hours after Iclusig oral administration. Food does not affect absorption of food. The aqueous solubility of ponatinib is pH dependent, with higher pH resulting in lower solubility.
When 45 mg of ponatinib is given to cancer patients, the pharmacokinetic parameters are as follows: 
Cmax = 73 ng/mL;
AUC = 1253 ng•hr/mL;
